VG. JAYAKUMARAs part of the monthly programme of Swati Tirunal Sangeeta Sabha, a veena concert by K.G. Vijayakrishnan was held at Kartika Tirunal Theatre, Thiruvananthapuram.K.G. Vijayakrishnan follows the Veena Dhanammal bani in playing the veena. Ragabhavais the main focus. K.G. Vijayakrishnan learnt the veena from his mother Karpagavalli Gopalakrishnan who was a disciple of the famous musicologist Rangaramanuja Ayyangar.Elaborate delineationThe main feature of K.G.Vijayakrishnan's veena concert was the famous composition of Muthuswami Dikshitar, `Balagopala' in Bhairavi. It was set to Adi tala. He gave an elaborate delineation of Bhairavi, bringing out its ragabhava. The thaniavarthanam was performed ably by B.Surendran on the mridangam and Trivandrum Kartikeyan on the ghatam.Earlier, K.G. Vijayakrishnan started with a varnam in Gananavaragamalika composed by Veena Kuppier set to Adi tala. This was followed by a Tyagaraja kriti `Rama Ninne Naminam' in Huseini raga set to Adi talam.The other compositions that K.G.Vijayakrishnan played included Venkata Subbaier's `Dhanyudevado' in Malayamarutham, Swati Tirunal's `JayaJaya Padmanabha' in Manirang, Syama Sastri's `Kamakshi' in Varali and Dikshitar's `Tyagarajaye Namasthe' in Begada.The veena concert concluded with a few thukkadas, which included, among others, the evergreen Swati padam, `Alarshara parithapam.'Bottom Template Starts
